        "execSummary":  "Google has materially upgraded its Gemini API agent runtime with background task execution and remote MCP server support, making it viable for enterprise production deployments rather than just prototypes. Organizations building agentic workflows on Google infrastructure can now run long-horizon tasks asynchronously and integrate external data sources without custom middleware. The remote MCP integration is strategically significant as MCP is fast becoming the interoperability standard for agentic AI tooling across vendors. Enterprises evaluating agent platforms should test these capabilities against their integration stack now, as the MCP ecosystem locks in quickly once tooling is built.",
