        "theme":  "Platforms",
        "summary":  "AWS announced the Claude apps gateway, a self-hosted control plane providing centralized access, cost, and policy management for Claude Code and Claude Desktop across enterprise development teams. The gateway eliminates the need for individual developer API credentials and manual settings distribution, while enabling spend limits per organization, group, or user. It integrates with existing identity providers through OIDC authentication and routes inference through Amazon Bedrock or Claude Platform on AWS.",
        "execSummary":  "The Claude apps gateway solves a real enterprise governance gap: as AI coding tools proliferate across dev teams, organizations have struggled with credential sprawl, runaway spend, and inconsistent policy enforcement. This self-hosted control plane gives IT and security leaders centralized visibility and spend controls without blocking developer productivity. The OIDC integration means it can slot into existing enterprise identity infrastructure with minimal friction. For leaders managing AI tool adoption at scale, this is a model for governed self-service ΓÇö the pattern that will be required before AI tools can clear enterprise security reviews broadly.",
