        "source":  "AWS Machine Learning Blog",
        "url":  "https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/machine-learning/build-a-semantic-layer-for-agentic-ai-on-aws-with-stardog-and-amazon-bedrock-agentcore/",
        "date":  "2026-07-10",
        "theme":  "Agents",
        "summary":  "This post demonstrates building a semantic layer on AWS using Stardog\u0027s knowledge graph federated across Amazon Aurora and Amazon Redshift, enabling an AI agent on Amazon Bedrock AgentCore to answer complex business questions without ETL processes. The architecture combines a foundation model, a governed semantic data layer, and a managed agent runtime to deliver reliable analytics across distributed enterprise data sources. The implementation eliminates the need to move or replicate data while preserving governance.",
        "execSummary":  "The semantic layer pattern described here ΓÇö knowledge graph plus vector-capable agent runtime atop distributed enterprise data ΓÇö solves the most common blocker to enterprise AI: fragmented, ungoverned data that agents cannot safely query. By federating across Aurora and Redshift without ETL, organizations can deploy agents over existing data infrastructure in weeks rather than months of data engineering work. This is strategically significant for enterprises with mature data warehouses looking to enable AI without a data migration program. The Stardog dependency adds a specialized vendor layer; organizations should assess whether native Bedrock Knowledge Bases cover their graph query requirements before committing to the full stack.",
