        "execSummary":  "The $234 billion SaaS disruption figure is a board-level decision trigger: organizations that lock in multi-year seat-based enterprise contracts today may find themselves paying for capabilities that AI agents have already automated, while outcome-based alternatives deliver higher ROI. Zendesk\u0027s pivot toward agent-outcome pricing directly signals how customer-support software vendors are repositioning ΓÇö enterprise leaders in this space should renegotiate contract structures now rather than at renewal. The vendors who capture institutional memory and cross-system context (not just single-app functionality) will dominate the next SaaS generation, making system integration and data continuity critical vendor selection criteria. This is a call to action for IT and procurement leaders to audit current SaaS portfolios against agentic capability gaps before 2027.",
